    "John Trapp": "Of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` and Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]`. ] Of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` by nature, of Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` by education and instruction. See #1Co 4:15 Ga 4:12 , { See Trapp on \"1Co 4:15\" } { See Trapp on \"Ga 4:12\" } So the Jesuits call themselves padres, and require of their novices blind obedience, which is more than ever Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` did.\nVer.\n1. Of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` and Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]`.] Of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` by nature, of Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` by education and instruction. See #1Co 4:15 Ga 4:12, {See Trapp on \"1Co [v_Gal_4_12] 4:15\"} {See Trapp on \"Ga 4:12\"} So the Jesuits call themselves padres, and require of their novices blind obedience, which is more than ever Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` did.\nVer.",
